  "description": "The two-chamber refrigerator from LG belongs to the middle price segment and is equipped with everything necessary for efficient operation, long service life and convenient use. It is designed in a minimalist style, painted in a rich dark gray color and has a fairly traditional layout: a refrigerator compartment on top, a freezer compartment on the bottom and two separate doors for them. The “heart” of the device is an inverter linear compressor, which is distinguished by its reliability, durability and energy efficiency. According to the manufacturer, its durability is confirmed by a 20-year life cycle test carried out by the VDE testing institute. LINEARCooling technology ensures uniform cooling throughout the chamber and helps keep food fresh longer by eliminating temperature fluctuations. And DoorCooling+ technology features vents located at the front of the refrigerator that help maintain the temperature at the optimal level. Inside, the LG GB-B92MCBAP has everything you need to properly organize your workspace. In the refrigerator compartment, in addition to the usual shelves, there is a 2-stage folding shelf, which frees up space for tall and bulky items. The FRESHBalancer zone maintains humidity levels for long-term storage of vegetables and fruits. The FRESHConverter department uses zero temperature for meat and fish. And the wine cabinet is designed to store up to 5 bottles of wine. The freezer has 3 compartments and can keep cold for 14 hours in case of power outage. In addition, the refrigerator boasts fast cooling and freezing functions, internal LED lighting, a touch control panel, the ability to hang the doors and an indicator that signals when the door is open.",
